 the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py:106:This PR improves dynamic-access coverage for {coordinates} by generating additional tests.\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2413:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2443:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2449:        \"dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2450:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2455:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2585:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2589:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2608:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2610:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2612:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3379:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5541:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5544:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5545:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:61:    \"\"\"Return the total covered dynamic-access call count from library stats.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:80:    \"\"\"Explain large dynamic-access/metadata-entry count differences in generated PR bodies.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:91:        \"### Metadata/dynamic-access evidence\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:93:        f\"- Covered dynamic-access calls: {covered_calls}\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:95:        \"- These counts are different dimensions: covered dynamic-access calls count observed call sites, \"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:107:        \"- Use the call-site and metadata-rule lists together to review whether the observed dynamic-access \"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:114:    \"\"\"Load covered dynamic-access call sites and generated metadata rules for PR evidence.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:125:        \"dynamic-access\",\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_new_library_support.py:126:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:718:    \"\"\"Return fully covered dynamic-access categories that became uncovered.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:751:    \"\"\"Fail PR publication if old/new stats show a dynamic-access category regression.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:770:    \"\"\"Format a single dynamic-access stats entry.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:779:    \"\"\"Return True when stats has the expected dynamic-access entry shape.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:797:    \"\"\"Format the dynamic-access stats into a markdown section.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:78:    \"\"\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py:94:                tracked_api=call_site_payload[\"trackedApi\"],\n./forge/utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py:160:        return \"All dynamic-access call sites are covered.\"\n./forge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:2:- Add or refine tests so execution reaches uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./forge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:3:- Keep coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated `{test_language_display_name}` test file under `src/test/{test_source_dir_name}` in `graalvm-reachability-metadata`.\n./forge/prompt_templates/persistent/dynamic_access_rules.md:4:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration-update.md:4:Extend the existing test suite for `{library}` to cover as many uncovered dynamic-access call sites as possible across all classes in the report below.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration-update.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:67:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:70:            \"Forwarded to add_new_library_support.py. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access strategies \"\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:71:            \"even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n./forge/benchmarks/benchmark_runner.py:217:        cmd.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:4:Improve test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `{library}`.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:13:Progress since the previous dynamic-access report:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:16:Remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites for this class:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:12:Full dynamic-access coverage report, all classes with uncovered call sites:\n./forge/utility_scripts/large_library_progress.py:246:        \"\"\"Record aggregate dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:98:  [--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access] \\\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:123:- `--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access` keeps generated tests for dynamic-access workflows even if no dynamic-access call sites are covered.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:383:coordinates, active dynamic-access classes, source-context paths, and Gradle\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:418:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:449:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:456:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:478:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:42:            \"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\\n\"\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:43:            \"[dynamic-access] Progress after org.example.SomeClass: \"\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:45:            \"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\",\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:498:                    \"prompts\": {\"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"unused\"},\n./forge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:592:                \"prompts\": {\"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"unused\"},\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:16:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:39:            self._print_message(\"no primary workflow configured, skipping to dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:50:                self._print_message(\"skipping dynamic-access coverage phase because primary workflow did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:56:        self._print_message(\"starting dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:65:            \"dynamic-access coverage phase completed with phase_ok={phase_ok}, iterations_added={iterations}\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:72:            self._print_message(\"keeping primary workflow result because dynamic-access coverage phase did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:26:    \"\"\"Bulk dynamic-access coverage strategy that shows the full report to the agent.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:28:    REQUIRED_PROMPTS = [\"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\"]\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:52:            \"dynamic-access\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:53:            \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:93:                \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:151:                self._print_detail(\"result: dynamic-access report unavailable after test run\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:155:                \"Optimistic dynamic-access coverage ({covered}/{total})\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:224:            \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:231:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_new_library_support.py:41:        self.assertIn(\"### Metadata/dynamic-access evidence\", body)\n"}], "isError":